name: Weighted Squats
text: This movement works your quads, glutes, and calves. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, dumbbells by your sides, palms facing each other.

name: Weighted Lunges
text: Dumbbell lunges are a weighted variation of forward lunges. Perform dumbbell lunges by holding a dumbbell in each hand as you take a big step.

name: Renegade Rows
text: he renegade row is an advanced row variation characterized by holding your body in a plank position with one hand while lifting a dumbbell.

name: Chest Press
text: The chest press is a classic upper-body strengthening exercise that works your pectorals (chest), deltoids (shoulders), and triceps (arms).

name: Box Jumps
text: Box jumps are a quintessential plyometric move where you jump from the floor up onto an elevated surface, like a box.

name: Power Lunges
text: Coaching Points. Stand with feet shoulder width apart. Lunge back with left leg so top of front leg is parallel to ground.
